In a press briefing, White House Press Secretary Sarah Sanders discussed various topics. She mentioned that President Trump and First Lady Melania Trump welcomed President Emmanuel Macron and Mrs. Macron to the White House for the first state visit of the Trump administration. They discussed economic, diplomatic, and global issues. Sanders also commended the actions of James Shaw Jr., who stopped an active shooter at a Waffle House in Tennessee. The President offered condolences to the victims and their families. Sanders also congratulated the Duke and Duchess of Cambridge on the birth of their third child. In regards to North Korea, Sanders stated that the goal is complete denuclearization of the Korean Peninsula, and that no sanctions will be lifted until concrete actions are taken. She also mentioned that discussions on the Iran nuclear deal will likely take place during Macron's visit. Sanders did not provide any updates on the case of Eric Garner or on the EPA Administrator Scott Pruitt. Finally, she expressed support for Mike Pompeo's confirmation as Secretary of State and criticized the Senate for delaying the confirmation process.